[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenDocument OpenDocumentFormat (ODF)] is an XML-based standard for the exchange of office documents. 

Documents stored in OpenDocument format carry the following extensions:
* Text - .odt 
* Presentation - .odp
* Spreadsheet - .ods
* Graphic - .odg
* Database - .odb

These documents are typically created with popular applications like [http://www.openoffice.org/ OpenOffice] and  [http://www.libreoffice.org/ LibreOffice].

DocViewMode can be used for [http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/emacs-devel/2010-12/msg00779.html viewing OpenDocument files]. 

Refer [[OpenDocumentText]] for working with .odt files.
